Architecture plan for the family doctor finder

Product scope
- Build a public-service family doctor finder for Canadian cities/areas.
- Users search by city/area, browse family doctor and clinic listings, see current accepting status with recency, view detail/report history, and submit anonymous confirmations or status-change reports.

Repository structure
- Root: shared README, .env.example, build/deployment scripts, formatting/lint config entry points.
- backend/: Rust Axum API server.
- backend/src/main.rs: server bootstrap, tracing, config load, router wiring.
- backend/src/config.rs: environment variables for DATABASE_URL, bind address, public/CORS origin, Nominatim endpoint, and rate-limit settings.
- backend/src/http/: routes, request extractors, validation, response/error mapping.
- backend/src/services/: city search, listings, report submission, status/recency derivation, geocoding orchestration.
- backend/src/db/: sqlx pool setup, repository functions, database models.
- backend/migrations/: sqlx migrations for cities/areas, doctors/clinics, availability reports, and seed data where appropriate.
- frontend/: React SPA.
- frontend/src/app/: router, app shell, providers, query client.
- frontend/src/api/: typed API client and React Query hooks.
- frontend/src/features/search/: home search and city typeahead.
- frontend/src/features/results/: list view, map/list toggle, recency indicators, report controls.
- frontend/src/features/detail/: doctor detail view and report history.
- frontend/src/components/: reusable UI primitives and state components.
- frontend/src/types/: shared frontend DTO types matching API responses.

Shared contracts
- Keep API DTOs explicit and stable: CitySummary, DoctorListingSummary, DoctorDetail, AvailabilityReport, DerivedAvailabilityStatus, SubmissionResult, ApiError.
- Prefer serde-compatible Rust response structs as the source of truth and mirror them in TypeScript manually until a later issue adds generation.
- Dates/times should be UTC ISO-8601 at the API boundary; frontend derives display text such as "confirmed X days ago".
- Listing status is derived from report history rather than stored as the authoritative fact. Store immutable reports and optionally cache denormalized last-confirmed metadata only if needed.

Issue dependencies and implementation order
- Foundation: #1 repository layout, #2 TypeScript/lint/format, #3 PostgreSQL/sqlx migrations, #4 environment config, #5 Axum baseline, #6 React app shell.
- Data layer: #7 cities/areas, #8 doctors/clinics, #9 availability reports, #10 status/recency service, #11 seed data.
- Backend API: #12 city typeahead, #13 Nominatim geocoding, #14 listings by city, #15 doctor detail, #16 confirm accepting, #17 report status change, #18 rate limiting/abuse safeguards.
- Frontend integration: #19 typed API client/hooks, #20 home search, #21 results list, #22 Leaflet/OSM map, #23 detail view, #24 one-tap controls, #25 submission feedback and optimistic recency.
- Hardening: #26 smoke test, #27 empty/sparse/error states, #28 self-hosted deployment preparation.

Key design decisions
- Use Axum with tower middleware, sqlx for async PostgreSQL access, and migrations committed under backend/migrations.
- Keep anonymous submissions append-only in availability_reports for auditability and to avoid destructive status edits.
- Derive accepting/recency in a backend service used by both list and detail endpoints, so frontend views stay consistent.
- Use Nominatim only through a backend client with caching and graceful fallback; do not block core listing pages on live geocoding success.
- Respect Ideavibes proxy headers: use X-Forwarded-Host/X-Forwarded-Proto or ALLOWED_CORS_ORIGIN for public-origin checks, never raw Host alone.
- Keep the React UI utilitarian and civic: accessible search-first entry, scannable results, clear recency/status states, and compact controls for repeated use.
- Use Leaflet with OpenStreetMap tiles for the map view while keeping the list view the primary reliable fallback.
- Add rate limiting before anonymous report endpoints are exposed in the UI.
